This paper deals with the optimization of energy efficiency in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for decomposing the problem, which involves system control (SY) and multimedia (MM) aspects. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of scheduling and power control, which is related to distributed computing (DC).
